content:
Give Users Access to Messaging for In-App and Web

To let agents message with customers, create and assign a permission set for Messaging for In-App and Web agents.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
This article applies to:	Messaging for In-App and Messaging for Web channels
USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To assign permission set licenses:	Manage Users
To create permission sets:	Manage Profiles and Permission Sets
To edit users:	Manage Internal Users
To assign permission sets:	Assign Permission Sets

Assign the Messaging for In-App and Web User permission set license.
From Setup, enter Users in the Quick Find box, and select Users.
Select the user you want to assign the permission set license to.
In the Permission Set License Assignments related list, click Edit Assignments.
Enable the Messaging for In-App and Web User permission set license.
Click Save.

Create a presence status for messaging.
Create a permission set for your messaging agents.
Select None from the License dropdown menu.
Click the name of your permission set from the related list, and select App Permissions. Click Edit, and check Messaging for In-App and Web Agent.
Save your changes.

Give Non-Agents Access to Messaging for In-App and Web Transcripts
To let non-agents view Messaging for In-App and Web transcripts,, give them access to the Messaging Session record and give them the Access Conversation Entries app permission.
title: Granting User Access to Service Cloud Messaging
